19) What is the difference between shallow copy and deep copy?
-->
| Feature         | Shallow Copy              | Deep Copy                 |
| --------------- | ------------------------- | ------------------------- |
| Object creation | New object                | New object                |
| Nested objects  | Shared (same reference) ❌ | New copies created ✅      |
| Independence    | Partially independent     | Fully independent         |
| Changes effect  | Affects both objects      | No effect on other object |
| Complexity      | Simple                    | More complex              |



20) Why is finalize() deprecated in Java 9 and later?
-->The finalize() method was deprecated in Java 9 because it is inherently unpredictable, dangerous, and inefficient
    Unpredictable Execution: There is no guarantee regarding when or even if a finalizer will run.
    Performance Impact: Objects with finalizers impose a significant overhead. The GC must perform extra work during both object creation and reclamation.
    Security Risks: Finalizers are susceptible to "finalizer attacks". A malicious subclass can override finalize() to resurrect partially initialized objects 
    that failed their constructor, allowing an attacker to bypass security checks and access sensitive data.



